    "says": "Squeeze more VMs on.",
    "means": "Allocating more virtual CPU/RAM to guests than the host physically has, betting they won't all peak at once. It saves money on general workloads but is dangerous for latency-critical ones (payments, databases) — the ratio is a per-tier design decision, not a global switch."
